[Course_Description]
Explore Adobe XD, the UX design platform for creating web apps and mobile apps using an iterative design process. Instructor Demian Borba shows how to set up a design project, use artboards and grids, and start working with vector design tools. Find out how to access user interface (UI) starter kits from Apple, Google, Microsoft, and the community. Discover how to use power capabilities such as Repeat Grid and the Assets panel, components with powerful overrides, leverage files from other apps and Creative Cloud Libraries, resize elements, use plugins, collaborate in real time, and more.